# New Feature Implementation Rule

When implementing a new feature, do not immediately modify the core flow.

First determine the safest extension strategy.

Prefer adding:
- new application service
- new use case handler
- new adapter
- new controller endpoint
- new module
- new event consumer
- new scheduled job
- new integration component

over changing central existing logic.

If existing main functionality must be changed, keep the change minimal and covered by tests.

Before coding, provide a short implementation plan:
- affected bounded context
- whether this is a module or microservice candidate
- existing functionality touched
- new contracts introduced
- tests to add
- migration needs
- observability needs

Do not perform broad refactoring unless explicitly requested.

If a new component becomes confidently independent, isolate it so that it can be extracted into a microservice later.

If it clearly meets microservice extraction criteria, propose a service boundary before implementing.